Summary: This document contains the timetable for the Master of Technology in Intelligent Systems course for the AY2023/2024 semester 1. The course will take place from July to November 2023 and will cover topics such as Integrity (L3), Autonomous Robots & Vehicles, and Human-Robot System Engineering. The course will be taught by lecturers Liu Fan, Nan Zhou, and Nicholas, and will take place on Saturdays from 9:00am to 5:00pm at the Integrity (L3) venue. The document also includes the timetable for the ISY5003 Graduate Certificate in Intelligent Robotic Systems course.

This document outlines the timetable for the MTech IS Course for AY2023/2024. The course will include lectures on Innovation I & II (L3), Momentum (L4), Blue Ocean (L4), and Influence (L3). The lectures will take place on Saturdays from 9:00am to 5:00pm, starting on 1 July 2023 and ending on 30 September 2023. The venue for all lectures will be Innovation I & II (L3). The course will also cover topics such as Conversational Uls, Aobo and Zhenzhen New Media and Sentiment Mining, Text Processing Using Machine Learning, and EBA5004 Graduate Certificate in Practical Language Processing Text

The document contains a timetable for the MTech IS course for the academic year 2023/2024. The course will be taught by various lecturers and will take place on Saturdays from 9:00am to 5:00pm. The courses include Ambition I & II, Blue Ocean, Momentum, Pinnacle, Integrity, and Horizon, with different lecturers and venues. There will also be a course on Advanced Machine Learning for Financial Services and Explainable and Responsible AI for Finance. The timetable is subject to updates.
